Key Match Events: David Wiese hit four boundaries to take 21 runs off Namibia's allotted Super Over.
Wiese starred with the ball for the Eagles, allowing just 10 runs while picking the wicket of big-hitting Naseem Khushi.

Mehran Khan gave just four runs off two overs in the final over, bringing up his wickets tally up from one to three in the first three balls of the final over, bowling Frylinck and trapping Zane Green lbw.
Trumpelmann trapped Oman opener Kashyap Prajapati lbw for a duck with a pinpoint yorker in the first over and bowled Aqib Ilyas unaware in the second over.
Bernard Scholtz leg before wicket Aqib Ilyas in the seventh over.
Post-Match Reflections: Mehran Khan's stunning spell helped Oman tie the game, but David Wiese's heroics in the Super Over gave Namibia a win in their opening ICC Men's T20 World Cup 2024 contest.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Namibia won the toss and decided to field first in Barbados.

Oman tried to pick the scoring rate when Namibia pacers arrived in the death overs, but David Wiese and Trumpelmann chipped away at the tail and bowled out Oman before they could complete their quota of overs.
